  "definitions": [
    "(intransitive) to joke, jest, be funny\nStai scherzando!  ― You are joking!",
    "(intransitive) to gamble, trifle, play"
  ],
  "description": "scherzare",
  "etymology": "Borrowed from Lombardic *skerzan (“to jump merrily, enjoy oneself, jest”) from Proto-Germanic *skertaną (“to hop, jump”), from Proto-Indo-European *(s)kerd- (“to dance, jump”). Akin to Middle High German scherzen (“to frolic, jump merrily, hop up and down”) (German scherzen (“to joke”); Scherz (“joke, sport”)), Norwegian skjerta (“to joke”). More at scherzo.",
